    "updated_at": "2017-02-20T19:31:55Z",
    "body": "Hi @marcatec, thanks for your feedback.\r\n\r\nWe definitely use feature requests to prioritize upcoming work. If you can share more about your application, and what it's trying to accomplish that helps justify the work. No promises, but every bit of information helps.\r\n\r\nAlternatively, we do accept community pull requests. For significant changes, we first like to discuss the proposed idea in the open, and allow community feedback. I would recommend using the [Rust RFC Template](https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/blob/master/0000-template.md) as a good place to start."
