    "updated_at": "2017-02-22T09:18:11Z",
    "body": "Hello @groundwater, I further investigated my case, and am not sure any more if it's a real feature request.\r\n\r\nWhat we want is similar to a feature in the app Svgsus, made with Electron.\r\nThey transform svg files via drag and drop, without dropping.\r\nIt can be seen in their video at time 0:17. http://www.svgs.us/images/svgsus_developer_video_web.mp4\r\n\r\nMy conclusion is, that is only possible loading the html page via file protocol.\r\nIn our app we use http (with a local server) and that case is restricted to provide the file info only on drop, not on dragenter or dragover.\r\n\r\nIs that behaviour hard coded into Chromium or is there a switch or can one be implemented?\r\nMay there be a chance to solve it using a custom protocol?\r\n"
  },
